# Jira Configuration

Use this configuration for Jira operations in this workspace.

Project Key: `MIS`
Project Name: `MissionaryJournal`
Project ID: `10148`
Project Type: `software`
Board Type: `kanban`
Cloud ID: `287a75f4-4fb2-497a-986e-82a5e566d271`
Site URL: `https://vulpelabs.atlassian.net`
MCP Server: `atlassian`
Auth Mode: `OAuth via Atlassian MCP`

Issue types:

- Epic: `Epic` (`10114`, hierarchy `1`)
- Story: `História` (`10116`, hierarchy `0`)
- Task: `Tarefa` (`10113`, hierarchy `0`)
- Bug: `Erro` (`10117`, hierarchy `0`)
- Subtask: `Subtarefa` (`10115`, hierarchy `-1`)

Default JQL scope:

```jql
project = MIS
```

When creating implementation stories from `docs/stories/`, create Jira issues in project `MIS` as `História` unless the user asks for parent `Epic`, generic `Tarefa`, bug `Erro`, or child `Subtarefa`.

Parenting rules:

- PRD Epic / AIOX Epic maps to Jira issue type `Epic`.
- Implementation stories map to Jira issue type `História`.
- Bugs map to Jira issue type `Erro`.
- Subtasks map to Jira issue type `Subtarefa` and require `parent`.
- In this team-managed software project, child issues use the Jira `parent` field for Epic/subtask relationships when available.

## Classification Standard

Every Jira issue created from this workspace must include both:

- `category`: one primary feature/functionality category.
- `tags`: Jira `Tag` field values used for area, domain, workflow, and traceability.

Use Jira fields directly:

- Category field: `customfield_10053` (`Category`)
- Tag field: `customfield_10246` (`Tag`)
- System labels field: `labels` (`Categorias`)

The Jira `Category` field currently returns no allowed values in metadata, so mirror category into system labels as `category-{category}` until the Jira field options are configured and verified.

Allowed categories:

- `memory`
- `workspace`
- `auth`
- `billing`
- `rules`
- `infrastructure`
- `devops`
- `docs`
- `qa`
- `ux`

Standard tags:

- `backend`
- `frontend`
- `fullstack`
- `database`
- `rules`
- `infrastructure`
- `devops`
- `docs`
- `qa`
- `ux`
- `memory`
- `tenant-scope`
- `routing`
- `layout-shell`
- `privacy`
- `media`
- `localization`
- `validation-reporting`

Tag and label rules:

- Use lowercase kebab-case only.
- Do not use accents, spaces, slashes, or punctuation.
- Always include `project-missionary-journal` in tags and labels.
- Always include `story` for `História` issues and `bug` for `Erro` issues.
- Always include one primary category value in `category`.
- Always mirror category to labels as `category-{category}`.
- Include one or more area tags such as `backend`, `frontend`, `fullstack`, `database`, or `rules`.
- Add feature/workflow tags only when useful.

Example story metadata:

```yaml
jira:
  issue_type: "História"
  category: "memory"
  tags:
    - "story"
    - "project-missionary-journal"
    - "backend"
    - "frontend"
    - "tenant-scope"
  labels:
    - "story"
    - "project-missionary-journal"
    - "category-memory"
    - "backend"
    - "frontend"
```

When creating the Jira issue through Atlassian MCP:

```json
{
  "additional_fields": {
    "customfield_10246": ["story", "project-missionary-journal", "backend", "frontend", "tenant-scope"],
    "labels": ["story", "project-missionary-journal", "category-memory", "backend", "frontend", "tenant-scope"]
  }
}
```

Only send `customfield_10053` after Jira returns allowed category values for the field.
